subSubSection.paragraph:
Anagyrus porteri (
Brèthes, 1921
)
(extralimital, included in the key) (
Figs 34–36
)

Taxonomic notes. This species was described from a single female. The flagellum has F 6 and the clava white ( Figs 34, 35 ), and the fore wing (
Fig. 36
) has three dark, transverse bands on the disc. The basal band behind the submarginal vein is very wide, the middle band behind the marginal and stigmal veins is narrow, and the apical band at wing’s apex is broader than the middle but narrower than the basal band.
